Imagines ac tituli et statuae:= As Aper is speaking of novi homines sine commendatione natalium, imayines cannot refer to the waxen images of ancestors, but rather to the so-called ‘clipeatae’ or ‘ argenteae imagines' which represented the Emperor or his amici or some distinguished man. Tituli were the inscriptions on these, hence joined by ac, i. e. imag. cum titulis et statuae.
